[SN]TITLE[SN]
Paraglider breaks leg in crash on Cairngorms hill

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A paraglider has broken a leg in a crash on a hill in the Cairngorms.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The person came down on Meall A' Buichaille, an 810m (2,657.5ft) hill above Loch Morlich near Aviemore, on Thursday.
Cairngorm Mountain Rescue Team and a coastguard helicopter went to their aid.
The paraglider was airlifted to Raigmore Hospital in Inverness.
